1.name: Season 1
1.overview: There are two groups, both consisting of five teams. Once the first group of five teams has served their dishes, and received a score, the next group of five teams then does the same. In the end, the team with the highest score from either group, will compete in the finals.

episodes.name: Episode 01 - Artie and Johnny (QLD)
episodes.overview:
The boys have been mates ever since Artie, 42, employed Johnny, 26, to work at his award-winning butcher shop - Nambour Plaza Meats – a few years ago.

Since then, Artie has inspired his young protégé to reach new culinary heights.

"I really started taking a liking to cooking when I was in high school," Johnny recalls. "But my passion for it grew when I met Artie. His love for food encouraged me to take it further."

Artie adds: "Food's always been a big part of my life. Being Mediterranean, i'’s who we are. Life’s about eating and enjoying food."

Both men take pride in the food they prepare and the meat they sell. Artie's butchery has been singled out for a Retail Excellence of the Year Award twice and his snags last year made the state finals of the Queensland Sausage King.

episodes.name: Episode 02 - Kane and Lee (VIC)
episodes.overview:
Hosting everything from tapas nights to dinner parties, Kane, 28, and Lee, 25, make one formidable duo. "We probably work better as a team than as individuals," Kane says. "We're not just team-mates, we're house mates and good friends."

They define their cooking style as Asianfusion with a twist. Growing up with a Chinese mother, Lee borrows heavily from her Asian heritage. "I always try to incorporate Asian ingredients into my food," she says. "Whether it's something simple like wombok, soy sauce or delicacies like black fungus – I always try and see what I can add to make it different."

episodes.name: Episode 03 - Sammy and Bella (NSW)
episodes.overview:
For Sydney sisters Sammy and Bella, cooking is a family affair. Their grandmother Ursula was a chef in Poland who cooked for many high-profile politicians including former US president Bill Clinton.

"She worked as a caterer for all the embassies so whenever there was a diplomatic event or a big political function she was part of the catering team," Sammy says. "She cooked for a lot of influential people, including Bill Clinton, which was the highlight of her career."

Bella adds: "Cooking is definitely in our blood. It's been passed on from one generation to the next in our family."

Not only have the sisters paired up for the competition but they used to work together in fashion; Sammy, 22, as a buyer and Bella, 27, in marketing. But in a strong indicator of their passion they both quit their jobs to take part in My Kitchen Rules.

episodes.name: Donna and Reade (SA)
episodes.overview:
The Adelaide couple have been running their own business for the last 12 years and use cooking as a means of escape from their work. They love it so much they even knocked down a wall in their home to create a bigger kitchen.

"We love the whole experience; everything from the shopping to the preparation and the actual cooking," Reade says.

Reade, 46, actually wanted to be a chef when he finished school but a mix-up cost him his dream. "I did my work experience as a chef and absolutely loved it," he explains. "The skills I have now are the skills I learnt during that time. I really wanted an apprenticeship at this restaurant but when I turned up they'd already offered it to someone else because they didn’t know I was coming."

episodes.name: Episode 05 - Melanie and James (TAS)
episodes.overview:
Melanie, 37, was married for 12 years to a chef who dominated their kitchen. "I didn't cook at all during that time," she says. "He just did it all. When we split up, I had to start cooking for myself and my two children. I found that not only could I cook, but I was pretty good at it too.

"When I was married I only had four dishes to my name. Now I have hundreds and I realise what fun I missed out on."

James, a 36-year-old jazz musician, was a notoriously bad eater. Tomato sauce on pasta was about as extravagant as he got. "I'd never had an interest in food until I met Melanie," he says. "I was like, 'Can you deep fry that?' Being a musician, a lot of the eating I did was between one and three in the morning."

episodes.name: Episode 06 - Daniela and Stefania (WA)
episodes.overview:
Their passion for food is infectious. "I just love to see people eat my food and enjoy it," Daniela says. "Cooking relaxes me. I could do it at 12.30 at night. Any time... I just love it."

Stefania adds: "We're Italian! Of course, we love our food. I enjoy seeing people's expressions when they taste the food I've made. It makes me happy."

The women are so close they're more like sisters. "We're very alike," Daniela, 43, says. "We like the same things. Stefania is fun to be with; everyone who meets her likes her."

Stefania, 41, is equally as kind about her cousin adding, "Daniela's a beautiful person inside and out."

The Perth duo get along so well they're worried it may pose a problem for them during the competition. "We muck around too much," Daniela says. "We find it hard to be serious."

Thrown straight into a challenge, the teams are tasked with catering for an inner city apartment block's annual warehouse party. The team with the best dish as voted by the residents will be the People's Choice and safe from the next elimination. The weakest team, as chosen by the judges, will head straight to the first sudden death cook-off.

episodes.name: MKR Kitchen HQ Challenge: Rapid Cook-Off
episodes.overview: Herbs are on the menu in the first rapid cook-off of the competition. One team has already won the People's Choice award, earning them safety from elimination, while the weakest team has been condemned to the first sudden death cook-off. The remaining teams must cook at Kitchen HQ for the first time where the judges have a few tricks up their sleeve. Who will rise to the challenge? And who will miss the mark? The team with the least impressive dish will go to the sudden death cook-off.

episodes.name: Sudden Death Cook-Off
episodes.overview: It's the first elimination at Kitchen HQ and the pressure is mounting as two teams battle for survival. With the arrival of the guest judges - Colin Fassnidge, Guy Grossi, Karen Martini and Liz Egan - getting it right will be even tougher, especially as all guest judges will be having bilnd tastings. And expect new judge Colin's tough love to send shivers through the teams. At the end of a frantic three courses, one team will be eliminated.

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Market Madness
episodes.overview: It's market madness for the remaining teams, who must open food stalls at the extremely busy Sydney Markets, which sees more than 40,000 visitors on the weekend. And in an extra twist, the People's Choice winners also receive a special surprise reward. The weakest team, as chosen by the judges, will head straight to the sudden death cook-off.

episodes.name: MKR Kitchen HQ Challenge: Breakfast Rapid Cook-Off
episodes.overview: Tonight, Breakfast is on the menu in the rapid cook-off. The remaining teams must cook at Kitchen HQ where the judges have a few tricks up their sleeve. Who will rise to the challenge? And who will miss the mark?

episodes.name: Sudden Death Cook-Off
episodes.overview: It's elimination night at Kitchen Headquarters and the pressure is mounting as two teams battle for survival. Having to impress guest judges Colin Fassnidge, Guy Grossi, Karen Martini and Liz Egan as well as Pete and Manu means getting it right will be even tougher.

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Taronga Zoo
episodes.overview: Tonight, teams are cooking lunch for hoards of school kids on a school excursion at Taronga Zoo. Teams will have to cook healthy kid-friendly food for 200 children. The best dish as voted by the kids will be safe from elimination, with the weakest team heading straight to the Sudden Death Cook-Off.

episodes.name: MKR Kitchen HQ Challenge: Joint Rapid Cook-Off
episodes.overview: In an MKR first, teams will join forces tonight to create a four-course meal during the rapid cook-off, and teamwork will be imperative, with all four teams from the losing group going into the showdown.

episodes.name: Sudden Death Cook-Off
episodes.overview: It's elimination night at Kitchen Headquarters and the pressure is mounting as two teams battle for survival. Having to impress guest judges Colin Fassnidge, Guy Grossi, Karen Martini and Liz Egan as well as Pete and Manu means getting it right will be even tougher.

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Melbourne Cup Day
episodes.overview: Tonight, the teams head to Australia's biggest race day, the Melbourne Cup, but it won't be all frocks and fascinators for our teams as they'll be cooking canapes for the prestigious Emirates Marquee's A-list guests. The team who wins best dish as voted by the guests will be safe from the next elimination.

episodes.name: MKR Kitchen HQ Challenge: 4 Ingredient Cook-Off
episodes.overview: The public has voted via social media and the four ingredients for the rapid cook-off have been decided. But the teams must decide among themselves who gets which ingredients. The bottom four teams will then have the opportunity to cook with their own favourite ingredient to impress the judges and avoid the sudden death cook-off.

episodes.name: Sudden Death Cook-Off
episodes.overview: It's elimination night at Kitchen Headquarters and the pressure is mounting as two teams battle for survival while trying to impress judges Colin Fassnidge, Guy Grossi, Karen Martini and Liz Egan, as well as Pete and Manu.

episodes.name: MKR Kitchen HQ Challenge: $10 Meal
episodes.overview: With just $10 to create a meal for four, the teams will form groups and combine their money to increase their purchasing power. But in a special twist, the teams in the opposite group will taste and score the dishes in a blind tasting. The team with the highest score will be safe from the next elimination, with the weakest team being sent straight to the next Sudden Death Cook-Off.

episodes.name: MKR Kitchen HQ Challenge: Winter Warming Challenge
episodes.overview: With winter just around the corner, teams are tasked with creating a winter warming dish in just 30 minutes. The bottom four teams will move into the Showdown to create their ultimate chocolate creation.

episodes.name: Sudden Death Cook-Off
episodes.overview: It's elimination night at Kitchen HQ and the pressure is mounting as two teams battle for survival. Having to impress guest judges Colin Fassnidge, Guy Grossi, Karen Martini and Liz Egan as well as Pete and Manu means getting it right will be even tougher.

episodes.name: MKR Comeback Kitchen
episodes.overview: Tonight, as teams are eliminated from Kitchen HQ, they're given one last shot in the MKR Comeback Kitchen. Eliminated teams will be put to the test in a real restaurant for a chance for a spot in the finals.

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Cable Beach
episodes.overview: The teams embark on an adventure to Western Australia to work with some of the freshest ingredients on offer. Their first port of call is Broome and the spectacular Cable Beach. Here teams must fish and catch as much seafood as possible, as the team with the heaviest load will have the first choice of ingredients to cook with as they prepare dinner over open fires for 40 tourists on spectacular Cable Beach.

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Margaret River
episodes.overview: The teams continue their west coast travels tonight, making their way south to the famed Margaret River region. Arriving at a beautiful winery, they must cook for 100 farmers celebrating the WA Farmers Association 100th anniversary in just 100 minutes.

episodes.name: MKR Comeback Kitchen
episodes.overview: MKR returns to the comeback kitchen as, unbeknown to the teams still competing, those who depart after a loss at the sudden death cook-off are given a chance for a spot back in Kitchen HQ. They'll be working in a real kitchen cooking for real paying customers at Colin Fassnidge's restaurant 4 Fourteen as he dishes out big serves of tough love. Judges Manu Feildel and Pete Evans will be doing blind tastings to decide which team will stay in the competition.

episodes.name: Offsite Challenge: Lunchtime Food Truck
episodes.overview: Teams must operate a food truck for a busy lunchtime service in Sydney's CBD. Judges Pete Evans and Manu Feildel will decide the best two dishes, giving the winners the opportunity to decide who they will compete against in the upcoming finals deciders.

episodes.name: Semi-Final: Round One
episodes.overview: The MKR competition heats up tonight with the first of the finalists decided by the end of the evening. The winner from last night's food truck challenge has chosen their two adversaries for tonight, and in a surprise twist they will also choose the ingredients that each team cooks with for the challenge.

episodes.name: Semi-Final: Round Two
episodes.overview: The competition continues to sizzle tonight as the second group of finalists is decided. The winner from Monday's food truck challenge has chosen their two adversaries for tonight, and in a surprise twist they will also choose the ingredients that each team cooks with for the challenge.

episodes.name: MKR Comeback Kitchen
episodes.overview: We return to comeback kitchen as the newly eliminated teams learn that they have a second chance to get them back in the competition. Tonight they'll be put to the test in a restaurant for real customers with real money under the watchful eye chef of Colin Fassnidge, who will be dishing out big serves of tough love. Manu and Pete will have a blind tasting to judge every meal to give one team a spot in the finals.

episodes.name: Semi-Final: Round Three
episodes.overview: Tonight, teams are shocked to see the return of one previously eliminated team - the winner from comeback kitchen. The five teams must create an Amuse Bouche - an elaborate bite- sized creation showcasing all the ability and craftsmanship of their team. Then, the bottom two teams will battle it out in a final cook-off for the last place in the final four.

episodes.name: Finals: Round One
episodes.overview: Tonight, teams must cook their ultimate three-course meal. With blind tastings from the guests judges, the pressure is on and teams are pushed to their limits as the finals heat up.

episodes.name: Finals: Round Two
episodes.overview: Tonight, teams must cook their ultimate three-course meal. With blind tastings from the guests judges, the pressure is on and teams are pushed to their limits as the finals heat up.

episodes.name: Grand Final
episodes.overview: Two teams go head to head in tonight's Grand Final as they work like never before to prepare a five-course meal for a full restaurant. With 100 plates to serve per team, the pressure is on. Judges Pete Evans and Manu Feildel will watch the teams in action, while guest judges Guy Grossi, Colin Fassnidge, Liz Egan and Karen Martini will blind taste each dish. The team with the highest score will be crowned the MKR 2013 champions and walk away with $250,000.

episodes.name: Grand Final
episodes.overview: On a night when humble home cooks become superstars, emotions overflow as both teams crack in very different ways. The best of the best compete for the title of 2017 MKR Champions and $250,000.

episodes.name: Josh & Nick (NSW Group 1)
episodes.overview: Pete and Manu are back again for Australia's most popular cooking show, My Kitchen Rules. This year, it's not just the teams who are opening their front doors!

episodes.name: Alex & Emily (QLD Group 1)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Miami on the Gold Coast where loved up hospitality couple Alex & Emily are aiming to raise the bar. But just as the party gets started, will it all come crashing down?

episodes.name: Roula & Rachael (VIC Group 1)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Melbourne where best friends Roula and Rachael are ready to serve up a fresh hit of hip-hop attitude. But is their confidence a ticking time bomb?

episodes.name: Kim & Suong (VIC group 1)
episodes.overview: Still in Melbourne, supermums Kim & Suong take to the kitchen to share the flavours of their Vietnamese heritage, while at the table a shock insult sparks the biggest blow up of the season!

episodes.name: Ash & Matty (QLD Group 1)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to the Sunshine Coast where surfie couple Ash & Matty are in the zone for their big debut. Will fish out of water Matty sink or swim on a night where sharks are circling at the table?

episodes.name: Stuss & Steve (QLD Group 1)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Brisbane where best buddies Stuss & Steve set out on a culinary odyssey. But will their big fat Greek feast be a big, fat fail?

episodes.name: Stella & Jazzey (WA Group 1)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Western Australia where "Perth's best waitresses" Stella & Jazzey are aiming to serve up a night to remember. Strap yourselves in for a rollercoaster night!

episodes.name: Jess & Emma (NSW Group 1)
episodes.overview: The elimination showdown is decided in the final Instant Restaurant of Group 1. Sisters Jess & Emma are promising a lip-smacking menu. But with old rivals out to settle a score, will they deliver?

episodes.name: Sudden Death Cook-Off (Group 1)
episodes.overview: The elimination twist is revealed and Colin Fassnidge returns as the bottom two teams of Group 1 face off in a sudden death cook off like no other.

episodes.name: Henry & Anna (TAS Group 2)
episodes.overview: Back by popular demand, truffle farmer Henry and his sister Anna are set to open the first Instant Restaurant of Group 2 on their family farm in Tasmania. Henry's hot property but can he cook?

episodes.name: Dan & Gemma (SA Group 2)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Adelaide where cricket loving in-laws Dan & Gemma are stepping up to the crease. But what leads to another walk out?

episodes.name: Davide & Marco (WA Group 2)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Sydney where Russian friends Olga & Valeria are determined to put the food of their motherland on the map. But when their only friends are enemies will the cooking comrades crumble?

episodes.name: Olga & Valeria (NSW Group 2)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Sydney where Russian friends Olga & Valeria are determined to put the food of their motherland on the map. But when their only friends are enemies will the cooking comrades crumble?

episodes.name: Georgie & Alicia (NSW Group 2)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Australia's home of big things, Coffs Harbour, where sisters Georgie & Alicia are planning to add a big score to the list. But will the confident siblings live up to expectations?

episodes.name: Matt & Aly (QLD Group 2)
episodes.overview: Teams are deployed to Brisbane where defence force foodies, Matt & Aly, are gearing up to impress the troops. But the real battle zone is at the table where rivals open fire.

episodes.name: Pat & Louisa (NSW Group 2)
episodes.overview: Teams travel to Sydney where mum and daughter, Pat & Louisa, are channeling their Hungarian gypsy roots to deliver a show-stopping menu. But does their crystal ball foretell fortune or failure?

episodes.name: Sonya & Hadil (NSW Group 2)
episodes.overview: It's the final Instant Restaurant of Group 2 which means it's time to shine for Sonya & Hadil. The ambitious friends are leaving nothing to chance but will their confidence be their downfall?

episodes.name: Elimination House (Group 2)
episodes.overview: The power to send our second team home is in the hands of Group 1 as they become guests and jury at MKR's Elimination House.

episodes.name: Elimination Challenge
episodes.overview: It's Group 1 vs Group 2 in an elimination challenge. The competition is turned on its head and new rivalries are forged when an epic first challenge sees the weakest team bring their whole group down.

episodes.name: High Tea Challenge (Group 1)
episodes.overview: High tea could be a low blow for some as Group 1 tackle the first location challenge - a high tea service where they'll be judged by the public - and their rivals.

episodes.name: Medieval Banquet Challenge (Group 2)
episodes.overview: Group 2 are tasked with serving a medieval banquet fit for a king; in fact two kings, Pete and Colin, as well as a huge table of lords, ladies, wenches, jesters and Group 1.

episodes.name: Elimination House (Group Challenge 1)
episodes.overview: The weakest teams from each Group Challenge meet at Elimination House where they face the biggest table of judges in MKR history. Which team will handle the pressure and who will send themselves home?

episodes.name: Home Delivery Challenge (Group 2)
episodes.overview: Group 2 are tasked with running a home delivery service; cooking, driving and delivering food to homes in the local neighbourhood. With the public and their rivals judging, who will fail to deliver?

episodes.name: Lawn Bowls BBQ Challenge (Group 1)
episodes.overview: Group 1 are set for some friendly competition as they celebrate two fun Australian pastimes - lawn bowls and a great BBQ! Which team will bowl 'em over and who will see red after a day on the green?

episodes.name: Elimination House (Group Challenge 2)
episodes.overview: The weakest teams from each Group Challenge meet at Elimination House. Sudden Death pressure can't kill the love in the kitchen, but the real pressure cooker is around the table.

episodes.name: Kids Sports Day Challenge (Group 1)
episodes.overview: Curtis Stone returns to MKR as Group 1 cooks for the toughest judges at a Kids Sports Day Challenge. With all these little mouths to feed who will be best and fairest and who will drop the ball?

episodes.name: Asian Street Food Challenge (Group 2)
episodes.overview: Group 2 is bringing the heat to Spice Alley, rocking the woks at their very own Asian street food stalls. With a paying public to please, one team stumbles in their own backyard.

episodes.name: Elimination House (Group Challenge 3)
episodes.overview: The weakest teams from each Group Challenge meet at Elimination House. One team will achieve perfection while the other will be sent packing in a heartbreaking sudden death cook off.

episodes.name: Pool Party Challenge (Group 2)
episodes.overview: Group 2 gets wet and wild at a pool party challenge. Who will make a splash on the barbie and which team will slip'n' slide into Elimination House? The fight for survival is fiercer than ever.

episodes.name: Picnic Challenge (Group 1)
episodes.overview: A picnic challenge is no walk in the park for Group 1. While they're packing baskets, rivals stick the knife in and one team has the rug pulled out from under them.

episodes.name: Elimination House (Group Challenge 4)
episodes.overview: The weakest teams from each Group Challenge meet at Elimination House. It's calm vs crazy in a clash of the titans and as one person spins out of control, a storm at the table blows up!

episodes.name: Romantic Dinner Challenge (Group 1)
episodes.overview: Group 1 don their chef whites to create dishes from the heart for the heart, serving up a romantic dinner. However with Manu as Head Chef, this restaurant takeover will leave one team brokenhearted.

episodes.name: Shared Lunch Challenge (Group 2)
episodes.overview: It's Group 2's turn to don their chef whites and serve share plates to groups of lunchtime diners. But things get hairy at this restaurant takeover and as Manu fires up, one team will go down in flames.

episodes.name: Elimination House (Group Challenge 5)
episodes.overview: The weakest teams from each Group Challenge meet at Elimination House. As one team's journey comes to an end, the other reaches unexpected heights - but not all the critics are impressed.

episodes.name: Icecream Challenge
episodes.overview: The biggest prize of the season outside the Grand Final is on offer to one of our Top 8 teams-to have their ice cream sold in Coles Supermarkets across Australia. Which team will lick the competition?

episodes.name: Super Dinner Parties 1
episodes.overview: The Super Dinner Parties are here and this year they're tougher than ever before. As the best of the best cook, one team will be thrown out of the competition.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Parties 2
episodes.overview: Baton down the hatches for the blow up which leads to one team leaving the competition for good.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Parties 3
episodes.overview: It's here! For the first time in MKR history, one team is asked to leave the table.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Parties - Stella & Jazzey (WA)
episodes.overview: Witness the fallout from the most controversial moment in MKR history! As the judges and teams regroup, it's time for Stella & Jazzey to get serious but their choice of bird has them in a flap.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Parties - Alex & Emily (QLD)
episodes.overview: It's time for loved-up cocktail couple Alex & Emily to shake up the kitchen but sometimes liquor and love don't mix. With one team down, is this the night we lose another?

episodes.name: Super Dinner Parties - Josh & Nic (NSW)
episodes.overview: In the penultimate ultimate, the hot-blooded Italian brothers turn on each other on a night of triumphs and take downs. Josh & Nic play hard but will the teams score fair?

episodes.name: Super Dinner Parties - Olga & Valeria (NSW)
episodes.overview: Olga & Valeria hope to blow away their rivals at their Super Dinner Party but some find their delicacies hard to swallow.

episodes.name: MKR Kitchen HQ
episodes.overview: It's out of the frying pan and into the fire as our Top 6 teams step into Kitchen HQ for the first time. The next four times they meet here, the strongest team will advance to the Semi Finals.

episodes.name: Quarter Finals 2
episodes.overview: Teams have another chance to go to the semi final. They'll compete over two rounds in tests of the imagination in a fight which tests the strongest relationships. Even the judges are at loggerheads!

episodes.name: Quarter Finals 3
episodes.overview: Teams have a third chance to advance to the Semi Finals. As they compete over two rounds, they deliver some of the best cooking we've seen but the strain of finals proves too much for one team.

episodes.name: Quarter Finals 4
episodes.overview: The competition will farewell two of your favourite teams as the Semi Final line-up is decided. With one place left, it's do or die as a cheating scandal sends shockwaves through Kitchen HQ.

episodes.name: Semi Final 1
episodes.overview: Colin Fassnidge, Karen Martini, Guy Grossi and Liz Egan join Manu and Pete for the first Semi Final. Teams have to deliver the best food of their lives if they want a place in the Grand Final.

episodes.name: Semi Final 2
episodes.overview: With only one spot left, dishing up food that splits the table is the last thing they need. It's high stakes and high stress on the Kitchen HQ battlefield where even the judges are up for a fight.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 1-1: Stacey & Ash
episodes.overview: It's the 10th Anniversary of MKR and to celebrate, our doors are open. For the first time, teams will be paired up in open homes to make a three-course menu for the public in Instant Restaurant.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 1-2: Amanda & Blake
episodes.overview: Can proud Perth siblings Amanda & Blake turn their humble beginnings into a grand finale? Meanwhile, Josh’s table manners go from bad to worse as the home schoolers refuse to learn a lesson.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 1-3: Karito & Ian
episodes.overview: Family heritage is on the line as Karito & Ian showcase the food and fire of her native Colombia. But will their Latin fiesta become a fiasco? Meanwhile, Ibby’s ready to confess.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 1-4: Chris & Lesley
episodes.overview: Flight attendants Chris & Lesley are planning to deliver a first-class night. But with such unruly passengers, turbulence is expected and it’s not just Chris & Lesley who are in for a bumpy ride.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 1-5: Andy & Ruby
episodes.overview: It’s MKR’s first Peruvian Instant Restaurant but will Andy & Ruby’s passion for their motherland get lost in translation?

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 1-6: Mick & Jodie-Anne
episodes.overview: In country Victoria, Mick & Jodie-Anne are all about serving champagne food on a beer budget. But they’ll have to show us what they’re made of and then some, as the table becomes a playground.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 1-7: Ibby & Romel
episodes.overview: The knives come out as Sydney socialites Ibby & Romel step into the kitchen. Can these controversial game players deliver or will they make a stylish exit?

episodes.name: Josh & Austin (NSW, Group 1)
episodes.overview: Teams have mixed expectations as they travel to Sydney for Josh & Austin’s Instant Restaurant. When the brutally honest brothers plate up, guests are left hangry and Manu’s just plain angry.

episodes.name: Lisa & John (WA, Group 2)
episodes.overview: MKR’s biggest fans host the biggest night ever, which includes two MKR firsts.

episodes.name: Victor & G (VIC, Group 2)
episodes.overview: Victor and G host a unique dinner party. Will their fusion food cause confusion?

episodes.name: Pat & Bianca (VIC, Group 2)
episodes.overview: There?s no love lost between frenemies Pat & Bianca, but when the pressure’s on can their love for food shine through? Plus, the shocking faux pas that crushes Karolina!

episodes.name: Anne & Jennifer (VIC, Group 2)
episodes.overview: The psychic and the cougar hope to conjure up a top scoring menu. But when the cards fall, will they read fortune or failure?

episodes.name: Lyn & Sal (SA, Group 2)
episodes.overview: South Australian friends Lyn & Sal are hoping to put Port Pirie on the map. But what’s a dinner party without its hosts?

episodes.name: Matt & Luke (NSW, Group 2)
episodes.overview: Cricket mates Matt & Luke are hoping to bowl everyone over with their spin on Mod Oz. But will their big bash turn into a sledging match? And could one team be playing dirty?

episodes.name: Veronica & Piper (NSW, Group 2)
episodes.overview: Beauty queens Veronica & Piper take centre stage. After promising perfection on their night of night, can they keep their crowns or will their tiaras tumble?

episodes.name: Milly & Karolina (VIC/WA, Group 2)
episodes.overview: Can perfect strangers team up to win MKR? Tonight – two become one in a history making Instant Restaurant. Can Milly & Karolina push their differences aside or will the night tear them apart?

episodes.name: Elimination Cook-off @ MKR Restaurant (Group 2)
episodes.overview: Group 1 return with the power to send our second team home at the elimination cook-off in the MKR Restaurant. Whose MKR dream will end tonight?

episodes.name: Most memorable Dishes Challenge
episodes.overview: Group 1 and 2 face off for the first time in a challenge celebrating the most memorable dishes in MKR history. One team’s failure brings their whole group crashing down. Which team will be going home?

episodes.name: Top 13 - Group 2 Pop Up Restaurant: Diner Challenge
episodes.overview: The first Pop Up Restaurant sees Group 2 serve diner-style food to the public, the judges and their rival teams in a buzzing retro games arcade.

episodes.name: Pop Up Restaurant
episodes.overview: At Bondi Beach, it's Group 1's turn for service while Group 2 ready themselves for revenge. In the battle of the brunches, one team will be toast!

episodes.name: Sudden Death Cook-Off 4
episodes.overview: The weakest teams to come out of the two group challenges meet at Elimination House.

episodes.name: Top 12 →Top 11 - Group 1 Pop Up Restaurant: Farmers Challenge
episodes.overview: Group 1 are tasked with turning farm fresh produce into fine dining and serving it to the farmers who grew it. Pete Evans and Colin Fassnidge are joined by guest chef Curtis Stone.

episodes.name: Pop Up Restaurant - Seafood Challenge (Group 2)
episodes.overview: Group 2 must produce a sophisticated seafood lunch for hungry sailors, but cooking in the elements takes its toll sending teams into choppy waters.

episodes.name: Sudden Death cook-off @ MKR Restaurant
episodes.overview: We’re back at the MKR Restaurant for a Sudden Death cook-off. It’s a passionate battle in the kitchen, while at the table accusations lead to an admission. With all this anger, will revenge be served?

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant - Open House
episodes.overview: For the first time ever on MKR, teams are paired up in mystery matches for a supercharged Instant Restaurant round. Teams are pushed to the limit as they take over houses and cook a three-course menu

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant - Open House (Andy & Ruby | Lisa & John)
episodes.overview: Peruvian friends Andy & Ruby and mother and son Lisa & John both topped their Instant Restaurant rounds, so expectations are high when they’re paired up for tonight’s Open House.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant - Open House (Matt & Luke and Pat & Bianca)
episodes.overview: Matt & Luke are paired with frenemies Pat & Bianca for tonight’s Open House, but the cricket mates aren’t prepared for such a volatile kitchen. At the table, an unexpected bond forms.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant - Open House (Mick & Jodie-Anne and Lyn & Sal)
episodes.overview: Teams escape to the country for tonight’s Open House where Mick & Jodie-Anne and fab friends Lyn & Sal are cooking with heart. As alarm bells ring in the kitchen, Josh sets fire to the table.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant - Open House (Josh & Austin and Veronica & Piper)
episodes.overview: Beauty queens Veronica & Piper join forces with brothers Josh & Austin for the last Open House. Can they put their differences aside and cook up a storm or will it be a beast of a night?

episodes.name: Sudden Death cook-off @ MKR Restaurant
episodes.overview: The two teams with the lowest Open House score face off at the MKR Restaurant. It’s panic stations all round as they fight to keep their MKR dream alive.

episodes.name: Coles Supermarkets Challenge
episodes.overview: Teams risk it to get the biscuit in a reward challenge with the prize of a lifetime - their winning creation produced and sold in Coles Supermarkets across Australia.

episodes.name: Craft Beer Challenge
episodes.overview: Teams crack cans at a craft brewery where cooking with beer is the order of the day. As some say cheers, others shed tears with the threat of going to elimination a sobering reality.

episodes.name: Moveable Feast Challenge
episodes.overview: Today's challenge is a moveable feast where each team is fighting to steer clear of elimination. Who will rise and whose hopes will go up in flames?

episodes.name: Top 8 cook-off @ MKR Restaurant
episodes.overview: A fierce battle rages at the MKR Restaurant with the final Top 8 position on the line. Whose MKR dream will end tonight?

episodes.name: Super Dinner Party - Matt & Luke (NSW)
episodes.overview: Opening batsmen Matt & Luke want to show how much they've grown as cooks. As they work on getting runs on the board, the table is on a knife-edge with teams caught out in a web of lies.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Party - Josh & Austin (NSW)
episodes.overview: The year's most explosive dinner party is here! We're back at Josh & Austin's bunker where they pray they'll redeem themselves. As three guests storm off, the biggest bombshell is at the table.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Party - Pat & Bianca (VIC)
episodes.overview: Pat & Bianca hope their menu can bring a fractured table together. But where there's smoke there's fire and the truth-seekers won't stop until they strike gold!

episodes.name: Super Dinner Party - Victor & G (VIC)
episodes.overview: Victor & G want to transform bad vibes into good energy. But as the barmen try to escape trouble in the kitchen, evidence at the table stacks up leaving Piper's heart in tatters.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Party - Lisa & John (WA)
episodes.overview: Expectations are high for Hall of Famers Lisa & John. As the history-making duo strive to recreate perfection in the kitchen, Victor lays it all out at the table exposing his lover's lies.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Party - Ibby & Romel (NSW)
episodes.overview: Cocky socialites Ibby & Romel are oozing confidence, but will pride come before a fall? Meanwhile a green-eyed monster takes a seat at the table.

episodes.name: Super Dinner Party - Veronica & Piper (NSW)
episodes.overview: With elimination looming, Veronica & Piper want to put on a night fit for a queen. But as the king of all scoring debates hits the table, can the beauties cook up a fairytale ending?

episodes.name: Super Dinner Party - Andy & Ruby (QLD)
episodes.overview: Confident Peruvians Andy & Ruby are striving to be numero uno but the Ultimates have challenged even the strongest of teams. Will their Latin fire be reduced to ashes?

episodes.name: The Golden Semi-Finals Ticket Challenge
episodes.overview: The MKR Restaurant is open for business but it's not all rave reviews on opening night. Which team will shine and score a golden ticket straight to the Semi-Finals?

episodes.name: Top 6 Semi-Finals Challenge
episodes.overview: The Top 6 teams step into the spotlight preparing show-stopping canapes for a room full of VIPs. Which delicious morsel will dazzle diners and send the winning team through to the Semi-Finals?

episodes.name: Toughest critics Challenge
episodes.overview: Teams face their toughest critics yet – the people who have walked in their shoes. Contestants from over 10 years of MKR return with big expectations. Which team will earn a place in the semis?

episodes.name: First Semi-Final
episodes.overview: Manu and Pete are joined by Colin Fassnidge, Karen Martini, Guy Grossi and Liz Egan at the MKR Restaurant for the first Semi-Final of 2019.

episodes.name: Second Semi-Final
episodes.overview: The pressure of Semi-Finals is at an all-time high, but so is the food and the smallest of mistakes could cost. Join Manu and Pete, alongside numerous guests, as the Grand Final line-up is decided.

episodes.name: MKR Champions 2019 (SEASON FINAL)
episodes.overview: A magnificent end to a milestone season as our two best teams of home cooks compete for the title of 2019 MKR Champions. In a series first, a panel of 10 judges in celebration of 10 years of MKR.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 1: Jenni & Louise
episodes.overview: For the first time in program history, it's chef versus chef and house versus house as five favourite teams go head-to-head with five new teams in the fiercest competition yet.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 2: Dan & Steph
episodes.overview: Season 4 Champions Dan & Steph kick things off for House Manu, but heavy is the head that wears the crown. Meanwhile, poker king Mark challenges Romel and takes strategy into the stratosphere.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 3: Ben & Vasil
episodes.overview: Bartending buddies Ben & Vasil get the party started for House Colin. While the amigos make their moves, spicy conversation leads to a Mexican standoff.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 4: Jake & Elle
episodes.overview: Season 4 runners-up Jake & Elle have their eyes on the prize for House Manu, but will their sibling spats stand in the way of success? Als, a love triangle is fuelled as romance blooms at the table.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 5: Sue Ann & Sylvia
episodes.overview: In a night of tears and tantrums, can childhood friends Sue Ann & Sylvia sing and dance their way to the top of the leader board for House Colin?

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 6: Jac & Shaz
episodes.overview: Season 6 runners-up Jac & Shaz feel the pressure to do well for House Manu. As the Mount Isa mums question their kitchen output, it's Sophia's performance at the table which gets everyone's attention.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 7: Kerry & Kaylene
episodes.overview: Ex-army sisters Kerry & Kaylene are going into battle for Colin. Can they charge to the top of the leaderboard or will they be outflanked? At the table, absent friends return with a vengeance.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 8: Roula & Rachael
episodes.overview: As besties Roula & Rachael set out to redeem themselves, the House of Manu is divided. Can Manu get his Faves back on track?

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 9: Mark & Lauren
episodes.overview: House Colin's high roller siblings Mark & Lauren have talked a big game but is it all just one big bluff? As the poker players' cards are revealed, Ben has a bombshell revelation of his own.

episodes.name: Instant Restaurant 10: Sophia & Romel
episodes.overview: It's the final Instant Restaurant and tough critics Sophia & Romel have to cook their butts off to avoid the elimination cook-off. Accusations fly in the most explosive dinner party yet.

episodes.name: Elimination Cook-Off 1
episodes.overview: House Manu take on House Colin in the first elimination cook off. And the truth is served with a side of denial as the two accused lovebirds face the music. Whose MKR dream will end tonight?

episodes.name: Top 9 - Faves Restaurant Takeover 1: Mexican Street Food Challenge
episodes.overview: It's the first restaurant takeover and House Manu are delivering Mexican street food in the hope of avoiding elimination. As Manu is pushed to the max, House Colin has more power than ever before.

episodes.name: Top 9 - Fans Restaurant Takeover 1: Asian Street Food Challenge
episodes.overview: House Colin has a score to settle and they've got their strongest cooks at the helm in this Asian street food challenge. But will their plans to keep out of elimination go up in smoke?

episodes.name: Elimination Cook-Off 2
episodes.overview: It's the second elimination cook-off of the season and there's a massive twist in store for the House on the chopping block. Which team will be eliminated tonight?

episodes.name: Top 8 - Faves Restaurant Takeover 2: Pub Grub Challenge
episodes.overview: A brand-new round of restaurant takeovers sees House Manu serving flash pub grub at the iconic Imperial Hotel. As the Faves feel the heat, the Fans hatch a plan and rival judges lock horns.

episodes.name: Top 8 - Fans Restaurant Takeover 2: Pub Classics Challenge
episodes.overview: House Colin's underdogs are serving sophisticated pub classics and they're pulling out all the stops to make their mentor proud in his own kitchen. Can one team's secret weapon save the day?

episodes.name: Elimination Cook-Off 3
episodes.overview: High expectations and revealing revelations in the third elimination cook-off of the season. In a shock head-to-head, which team will be sent home?

episodes.name: Top 7 - Faves Restaurant Takeover 3: Modern Australia Challenge
episodes.overview: A new round of restaurant takeovers sees House Manu take on Modern Australian. As the Faves try to deliver the wow factor, a new alliance could change the course of the competition forever.

episodes.name: Top 7 - Fans Restaurant Takeover 3: Modern Australia Challenge
episodes.overview: It's the elimination decider for House Colin. Kerry and Kaylene attempt to make a true-blue dish, while others sing for their supper.

episodes.name: Elimination Cook-Off 4
episodes.overview: The competition heats up as two teams battle it out, but only one team will stay.

episodes.name: Top 6 - Faves Restaurant Takeover 4: Fine Dining Challenge
episodes.overview: House Manu tackle fine dining in a round of Restaurant Takeovers. With tensions, tears, tantrums and one mighty bombshell, it'll be a night to remember for all the wrong reasons.

episodes.name: Top 6 - Fans Restaurant Takeover 4: Fine Dining Challenge
episodes.overview: House Manu is out for revenge, and rivalries get personal as House Colin tackles the fine dining Restaurant Takeover. Will the new recruits be their saviour, or will the fans fail?

episodes.name: Elimination Cook-Off 5
episodes.overview: The allied powers have a plan for this episode's elimination, but they're not the only ones playing dirty. Who will survive the chop, and who will get away with murder?

episodes.name: Top 5 - Finals Decider: Family Barbecue Challenge
episodes.overview: The Finals decider is here! The pressure is on as teams fire up the barbie for some very special guests. But when it comes to scoring time, will there be foul play?

episodes.name: Semi-Final - Ultimate Instant Restaurant 1: Dan & Steph
episodes.overview: It's finals time! Instant Restaurants are back as our top four teams compete for a place in the final. But the knives are out and revenge is on the menu when old friends return to play judge and jury.

episodes.name: Semi-Final - Ultimate Instant Restaurant 2: Kerry & Kaylene
episodes.overview: It's the second Instant Restaurant of the finals, and the pressure is at an all-time high for this episode's cooking team. Around the table, the judges raise questions, and temperatures soar.

episodes.name: Semi-Final - Ultimate Instant Restaurant 3: Jake & Elle
episodes.overview: For this episode's cooking team, old habits die hard; will it bring their grand final hopes undone? At the table, a big announcement, one last game of strategy, and a shock confession.

episodes.name: Semi-Final - Ultimate Instant Restaurant 4: Mark & Lauren
episodes.overview: The last Instant Restaurant of the Finals. Tonight’s team have a strategy to win, but will their confidence be their undoing? Expect a night of surprises as the Grand Final line up is decided.

episodes.name: Grand Final
episodes.overview: The Grand Finalists open their own restaurant on Sydney Harbour, where each team will create a four-course menu in the battle to be crowned ultimate champions and win $100,000.

11.name: Season 11
11.overview: For the first time in program history, it's chef versus chef and house versus house as five favourite teams go head-to-head with five new teams in the fiercest competition yet.

episodes.name: Episode 1
episodes.overview: A number of teams of amateur chefs hit the kitchen in an attempt to impress judges Nigella Lawson and Manu Feildel

episodes.name: Episode 2

12.name: Season 12
12.overview: After a one-year hiatus, the popular program is returning for its 12th season in 2022 with some big changes but still plenty of drama and delicious dishes. Feildel will be returning, joined by none other than British cooking royalty, Nigella Lawson. Former MasterChef Australia judge Matt Preston has also been announced as another judge. Colin Fassnidge, who has been a guest judge on MKR over the years, will be returning to do just that. Plus, Curtis Stone is also joining as a guest judge.
